WEBVTT

00:10.637 --> 00:12.905
I guess after
25 years of me,
she's had enough.

00:12.939 --> 00:14.773
Do you hope
things will work out
with Ricky and me?

00:14.808 --> 00:16.775
I've told you
more than once that
it won't work out

00:16.810 --> 00:18.710
if you just
move in there without
any kind of commitment.

00:18.745 --> 00:21.491
Hey, I'm sorry about the move,
but I talked to Grant
and he's cool with it.

00:21.525 --> 00:23.627
<i>What move?</i>

00:23.661 --> 00:25.823
I told Jack he could move
into the house and take Tom's
old room until school's out.

00:25.858 --> 00:28.923
You felt the same way
when I moved into the guest
house, and nothing happened.

00:28.957 --> 00:31.861
I still don't like
your living in the house
in the bedroom next to Grace.

00:31.895 --> 00:33.836
I got married
because I had to get married.

00:33.870 --> 00:35.713
And no, I do not
want to be married.

00:35.747 --> 00:38.716
I don't think
I'd say anything about
this stuff to anyone else.

00:38.751 --> 00:39.885
I want out.

00:39.920 --> 00:41.586
I'm afraid
he's going to
leave me.

00:41.621 --> 00:42.588
I keep telling everyone
he won't...

00:42.622 --> 00:43.790
But I'm afraid he will.

00:43.824 --> 00:45.597
Apparently Camille
is in love with you.

00:45.632 --> 00:47.500
That's why she quit.
What?

00:47.534 --> 00:50.905
I want you to be
honest with me and not
keep anything from me,

00:50.939 --> 00:53.811
and I want to be free to be
honest with you and not keep
anything from you.

00:53.846 --> 00:55.747
I really would like
to go and talk
to your dad.

00:55.781 --> 00:57.750
I don't want your family
to be upset with us.

01:01.958 --> 01:03.760
Come on, John,
Grandma's here.

01:03.795 --> 01:06.764
Why is Grandma
here so early?
We don't know.

01:08.768 --> 01:11.637
Oh, that's Grandmas.

01:11.671 --> 01:12.739
Two of them.

01:12.773 --> 01:14.642
Looks like you were
right, Margaret.

01:14.676 --> 01:16.611
Good morning.
Good morning.

01:16.646 --> 01:18.682
What's going on?
Is everything okay?

01:18.716 --> 01:20.751
Oh, no.
"Oh, no" is right.

01:20.785 --> 01:24.523
Ricky, don't you think
it'd be appropriate
to tell your mothers

01:24.558 --> 01:26.792
when you decide to make
a big decision like this?

01:26.827 --> 01:27.960
And your father?

01:27.994 --> 01:29.562
Big decision like what?

01:29.596 --> 01:31.831
Uh, like you two
are cohabitating.

01:31.865 --> 01:35.902
Not us two. Us three.
It's the three of us.

01:35.936 --> 01:39.574
Yeah, we decided
we didn't want to make
any big announcement.

01:39.608 --> 01:40.976
We didn't want it
to be a big deal.

01:41.010 --> 01:42.578
Because it's not
a big deal.

01:42.612 --> 01:43.979
Yeah? So, if it's
not such a big deal,

01:44.014 --> 01:47.918
why couldn't you just
tell us that you three
were living together?

01:47.952 --> 01:49.686
What she said.

01:52.757 --> 01:53.824
How'd you find out?

01:53.859 --> 01:55.626
Same way I find
everything out.

01:55.661 --> 01:56.828
People tell me things.

01:56.862 --> 01:58.898
Not people like you two,
but other people.

01:58.932 --> 02:00.700
What people?
We haven't told anyone.

02:00.734 --> 02:02.803
Actually,
some of us have.

02:03.939 --> 02:05.506
Adrian told you?

02:05.541 --> 02:06.875
I don't disclose
my sources.

02:06.909 --> 02:10.478
Just one of the reasons
people are comfortable
talking to me.

02:10.513 --> 02:12.680
And it doesn't
matter who told me.

02:12.715 --> 02:15.817
I heard it
from someone
other than you,

02:15.851 --> 02:17.719
and that doesn't
make me too happy.

02:17.753 --> 02:19.554
And let me
tell you something,

02:19.588 --> 02:20.855
your father isn't very
happy about this either.

02:20.889 --> 02:22.857
In fact, he was
gonna come with us,

02:22.891 --> 02:24.825
but he had a surgery
to perform this morning.

02:24.860 --> 02:27.828
You're not married to him,
she's married to him.
Shouldn't she me that?

02:27.863 --> 02:29.530
I'm telling you that.

02:29.564 --> 02:30.931
Has Ollie weighed in on this?

02:30.965 --> 02:33.567
How's your girlfriend
or fiancee or
whatever she is...

02:33.602 --> 02:34.669
How does she
feel about it?

02:34.703 --> 02:35.837
I haven't mentioned
this to Ollie.

02:35.871 --> 02:37.707
I don't know how
she's going feel about it.

02:37.741 --> 02:39.609
I don't care
how she feels about it.

02:39.643 --> 02:41.812
And as much as
I love you both
and my dad,

02:41.846 --> 02:43.615
I don't care how
you feel about it either

02:43.649 --> 02:46.618
because this is what
we want to do, so this
what we're doing.

02:46.652 --> 02:48.988
Uh... I care.
I care what you think.

02:49.022 --> 02:51.624
I also care
what my dad thinks

02:51.658 --> 02:54.695
and he's not too happy
about it either,

02:54.729 --> 02:56.764
and I feel terrible
about that, but...

02:57.699 --> 02:58.966
I really love being here.

02:59.001 --> 03:03.939
I mean, I love Ricky
and we both love John

03:03.974 --> 03:06.910
and we both love you...

03:06.945 --> 03:08.979
And we both have to
get to school.

03:09.848 --> 03:10.848
Bye.

03:11.917 --> 03:13.785
Say "bye," John.
Bye-bye.

03:13.820 --> 03:16.555
Bye-bye. Bye-bye.
Bye, John.

03:17.957 --> 03:19.925
Bye.
JOHN: Bye-bye.

03:25.766 --> 03:27.000
He's so cute.

03:28.002 --> 03:29.636
He is.

03:29.671 --> 03:30.738
Ricky.

03:30.772 --> 03:32.706
John.
But Ricky's cute too.

03:32.741 --> 03:36.644
Oh! And you know,
you're right, Amy does
look like you.

03:36.679 --> 03:38.880
I know.
It's kind of sick, isn't it?

03:38.914 --> 03:40.648
Oh, a little.

03:41.016 --> 03:43.518
So, what do you think?

03:43.552 --> 03:45.586
I think I hope
Ricky doesn't mess this up.

03:45.621 --> 03:47.789
Ricky? Hope Ricky
doesn't mess it up?
What about Amy?

03:47.823 --> 03:49.624
Oh, Amy's not going
to mess this up.

03:49.658 --> 03:51.959
No. Unless, of course,
at some point she
wants a real commitment.

03:51.994 --> 03:54.763
At which point,
it could all fall apart.

03:54.797 --> 03:56.932
Well, after they've
lived together for a while,

03:56.966 --> 03:59.902
maybe they'll want
to make a commitment
to each other.

03:59.937 --> 04:03.473
I mean, I don't think
this is the worst idea.

04:03.507 --> 04:05.475
I wish I had
known, but...

04:05.509 --> 04:06.909
Maybe this is
the right thing for them.

04:06.944 --> 04:10.580
You know Ricky has issues.
Especially with commitment.

04:11.882 --> 04:14.884
I don't know
if he can be
with just one girl.

04:14.919 --> 04:17.620
I think Ricky can
make a commitment.

04:17.654 --> 04:20.524
I think what he's doing
here is a commitment.

04:21.625 --> 04:24.661
Seems to me
you're the one that is...

04:24.696 --> 04:27.664
I told you I do not
want to talk about that.

04:27.699 --> 04:29.733
...unable to make
a commitment.

04:29.767 --> 04:31.901
I don't know why
you can't just work
something out

04:31.936 --> 04:33.570
so that Ollie is...

04:33.604 --> 04:34.904
Not going to talk about it.

04:34.938 --> 04:36.672
She loves you.

04:37.774 --> 04:39.842
(SIGHS) All right.

04:40.778 --> 04:41.978
I got to go.

04:42.012 --> 04:44.780
Oh, when you see
Ricky this afternoon,

04:44.815 --> 04:47.583
don't give him any
ideas about Amy
wanting a commitment,

04:47.617 --> 04:49.952
because maybe she does
and maybe she doesn't.

04:49.986 --> 04:51.787
Just let that be
between the two of them

04:51.821 --> 04:55.590
and don't let your
own issues cross
over into their lives.

04:55.625 --> 04:56.792
Or what?

04:56.826 --> 04:59.661
Or this little arrangement
he has with Amy

04:59.695 --> 05:01.530
could be the
beginning of the end

05:01.564 --> 05:04.599
instead of the beginning
of the beginning.

05:06.869 --> 05:07.869
Bye, Mom.

