05:54.991 --> 05:55.991
Hi.

05:56.226 --> 05:57.293
Hi.

05:57.327 --> 05:59.996
Katelyn O'Malley.
Okay.

06:00.030 --> 06:02.098
I'm the school counselor.

06:02.132 --> 06:05.268
Oh. I'm sorry.
I thought you
were a student.

06:05.302 --> 06:08.171
Excuse me.
Leo Boykewich,
nice to meet you.

06:09.340 --> 06:10.373
Could I talk to you?

06:10.408 --> 06:12.976
I only have a few minutes.
In my office?

06:18.382 --> 06:20.951
Please, sit down.

06:20.985 --> 06:23.220
I don't really
have time to

06:24.055 --> 06:25.156
sit down.

06:26.291 --> 06:28.092
I'm a little concerned
about Ben.

06:28.126 --> 06:30.261
We've all been a little
concerned about Ben.

06:30.295 --> 06:32.930
But he's doing all right
in school, isn't he?

06:32.964 --> 06:34.998
He is, he's making
a real effort

06:35.033 --> 06:36.266
to make up for
the time he lost.

06:36.300 --> 06:38.135
Good, good to hear.

06:38.169 --> 06:41.271
He's done really well,
considering what he
and Adrian went through,

06:41.305 --> 06:43.306
but it just seems
that he's

06:44.208 --> 06:45.342
increasingly

06:46.344 --> 06:47.378
agitated.

06:47.412 --> 06:49.380
Considering what
happened to them,

06:49.414 --> 06:52.116
it seems normal
he'd be agitated,
don't you think, Katelyn?

06:52.151 --> 06:54.051
I suppose so, yes.

06:54.086 --> 06:56.354
But he's getting more
and more agitated.

06:56.389 --> 06:59.324
Kind of building up steam
like he might,

06:59.358 --> 07:02.894
I don't know,
lose control or something.

07:02.929 --> 07:05.296
I just wondered
if there's anything
I can do.

07:05.331 --> 07:07.065
No, I don't think so.

07:07.099 --> 07:09.334
He's been getting
some help.

07:09.368 --> 07:11.302
And that's confidential
between you and me.

07:11.336 --> 07:14.272
Of course.
And that's good to hear.

07:14.306 --> 07:17.908
So, is Adrian also
getting some help?

07:17.943 --> 07:21.112
Because I would
love to get her back in
school by end of the year.

07:21.146 --> 07:23.280
I mean, if she came
back now and she
went to summer school,

07:23.314 --> 07:25.182
she might still
be able to graduate
this summer.

07:25.216 --> 07:26.950
I can't really
answer for Adrian.

07:26.985 --> 07:29.053
You'll have to ask Adrian
or her parents.

07:29.087 --> 07:30.188
Or Ben even.

07:30.222 --> 07:32.023
I talked to Ben,
he told me to call her,

07:32.058 --> 07:33.925
but she won't return
any of my phone calls.

07:33.960 --> 07:35.227
And I don't want
to just show up.

07:35.262 --> 07:36.395
You might have to.

07:36.429 --> 07:38.130
My wife, Betty,
did that last week.

07:38.165 --> 07:41.034
She went over there
and talked to her,

07:41.068 --> 07:43.270
and I think
she made Adrian
feel a little better.

07:43.304 --> 07:47.407
So you want to
show up, show up.
It's up to you.

07:47.442 --> 07:51.078
I've never been one
to just show up
somewhere myself,

07:51.112 --> 07:56.050
but sometimes maybe
it's the only thing to do.

07:59.153 --> 08:00.253
Hey, there he is.

08:00.288 --> 08:02.055
Yeah. Here I am.

08:02.089 --> 08:04.891
Could we use
your office for a
moment? You mind?

08:04.925 --> 08:06.125
I...

08:06.160 --> 08:07.960
I guess not.

08:08.929 --> 08:10.163
Hi, Ben.

08:14.302 --> 08:16.137
What are you
doing here?

08:16.171 --> 08:18.272
I thought I'd come by
and see if you wanted to
get out for the day.

08:18.306 --> 08:20.341
It's Friday,
the end of week.

08:20.376 --> 08:22.911
Maybe you wanted
to take the rest of
the day off, like me.

08:22.945 --> 08:24.980
No. I don't want
to take the day off.

08:25.015 --> 08:26.348
I don't want to get out
for the rest of the day.

08:26.382 --> 08:28.150
I can't get out for
the rest of the day.

08:28.184 --> 08:30.118
I've already missed
a lot of school and
I'm still catching up.

08:30.153 --> 08:32.354
Your counselor just
told me that you were
pretty much caught up.

08:32.388 --> 08:34.155
I just thought
we could hang out.

08:34.190 --> 08:36.124
I'm not caught up.

08:36.159 --> 08:39.061
You want out
of your office so badly
that you'd come over here

08:39.095 --> 08:41.297
and try to get me out
of class so you'd have
someone to hang out with?

08:41.331 --> 08:43.999
It's just that
I can't go through
another weekend

08:44.034 --> 08:45.167
without asking you something.

08:45.201 --> 08:46.969
Something you couldn't
just call me about?

08:47.003 --> 08:48.103
I called you.

08:48.138 --> 08:49.371
I didn't get any messages
that called me.

08:49.406 --> 08:51.240
Well, I didn't want
to leave a message.
What?

08:51.274 --> 08:54.109
I never know who
you're around
when I call.

08:54.144 --> 08:56.979
Most of the time
you're at your condo
and Adrian's there,

08:57.013 --> 08:59.181
and at the shop,
Bunny's there, and Ricky.

08:59.215 --> 09:00.983
So next time
just text me.

09:01.017 --> 09:02.251
No one's reading
my text messages,

09:02.285 --> 09:04.019
and I erase them
as soon as I get them.

09:04.054 --> 09:05.955
It's good to know. Still,

09:05.989 --> 09:08.257
I don't want any record
of anything regarding this.

09:08.291 --> 09:09.892
Regarding what?

09:09.927 --> 09:10.960
You know what.

09:13.164 --> 09:15.064
Camille?

09:15.099 --> 09:17.300
You still want to talk
about Camille?

09:17.334 --> 09:19.902
Did you come all the way
over here to my high school

09:19.937 --> 09:23.039
and drag me out of class
to find out if a girl
really likes you?

09:23.073 --> 09:27.978
I can't get
our conversation
out of my mind.

09:28.012 --> 09:31.382
I mean, are you sure
about this theory
regarding Camille?

09:31.416 --> 09:33.284
Dad, I just rushed
through a test

09:33.318 --> 09:35.353
and lied to my teacher
and told her I wasn't
feeling well

09:35.387 --> 09:37.155
so I could come out
here and talk to you.

09:37.189 --> 09:39.024
And I don't even think
she believes me,

09:39.058 --> 09:40.325
but no one is saying
no to me right now

09:40.360 --> 09:42.261
because everyone feels
so sorry for me.

09:42.295 --> 09:46.065
And because they think
you're increasingly agitated.

09:46.099 --> 09:47.133
(STAMMERS)

09:49.036 --> 09:50.403
I thought
you weren't coming in
until tomorrow.

09:50.437 --> 09:52.038
Why didn't you call me?

09:56.010 --> 09:57.210
I can't wait
to see you.

09:57.244 --> 09:58.278
I'll leave right now,
I'll come over there.

09:58.312 --> 10:00.347
Oh. I'm not home.
I wanted to see Adrian.

10:00.381 --> 10:02.949
Okay, well, when
are you leaving there?

10:02.984 --> 10:06.352
I don't know, but...
It's my first day back,
so it's been a little crazy.

10:06.386 --> 10:09.322
Still, you want
to see me, right?
It's been two weeks.

10:09.356 --> 10:12.158
I know,
a long two weeks,

10:12.192 --> 10:15.128
but I'm just
completely jet-lagged,

10:15.162 --> 10:17.096
so when I leave here,
I'll probably just
go home and crash.

10:17.130 --> 10:18.197
I'll crash with you.

10:18.231 --> 10:20.199
Grant, I want
to see you, I do,

10:20.233 --> 10:23.001
but I just need a day, okay?

10:23.035 --> 10:25.336
I just need to go
home and sleep
and clean up

10:25.371 --> 10:27.205
and I need to
see my mom.

10:27.240 --> 10:28.407
So let's just see
each other tomorrow.

10:28.441 --> 10:30.376
You said
there was nothing
we could do about it!

10:30.410 --> 10:32.278
We! That includes you.

10:32.312 --> 10:34.046
And by the way,
do you think doing nothing

10:34.081 --> 10:37.384
is not just going to make me
increasingly agitated?

10:37.418 --> 10:40.087
Look, I couldn't
do anything about
losing Mercy,

10:40.121 --> 10:41.388
but I can do something
about losing me.

10:48.096 --> 10:50.097
You told him
I said that?

10:51.299 --> 10:53.434
I didn't say it was you,
no, course not.

10:54.503 --> 10:56.270
But he may be right.

11:01.209 --> 11:03.110
Grace, I don't want
to wait till tomorrow
to see you.

11:03.145 --> 11:05.179
Well, I wasn't
going to be back
until tomorrow anyway.

11:05.213 --> 11:07.948
Yeah, when were you
going to let me know
you got in early?

11:07.983 --> 11:09.083
If Jack hadn't
said anything,

11:09.117 --> 11:10.250
I wouldn't even know
that you're back.

11:10.285 --> 11:12.186
Well, I am,

11:12.221 --> 11:13.321
and tomorrow night,
when you had planned
to see me,

11:13.355 --> 11:15.289
you will see me, okay?

11:15.324 --> 11:16.457
I have to go,
I'm at Adrian's.

11:18.093 --> 11:19.160
I'll talk to you
later, okay?

11:23.098 --> 11:24.232
He hung up on me.

11:24.266 --> 11:26.133
Finally.

11:26.168 --> 11:29.370
I mean, I feel badly,
but I really wanted
to see you first.

11:32.074 --> 11:33.374
Here I am.
Here you are.

11:34.276 --> 11:35.442
Yeah.

11:37.412 --> 11:40.247
Thanks for
coming over, Grace,

11:40.282 --> 11:42.316
but it's hard
for me to see you

11:42.350 --> 11:45.053
or to see anyone
when I look this.

11:45.087 --> 11:46.421
When you look like what?
Fat.

11:46.455 --> 11:48.457
Adrian, you just...

11:48.491 --> 11:50.091
Yeah,

11:50.126 --> 11:52.094
I just had a baby.

11:52.128 --> 11:53.262
Sorry.

11:54.164 --> 11:55.365
In a weird way,

11:56.500 --> 11:59.135
I like being fat.

11:59.169 --> 12:01.104
It makes me feel
like I'm still pregnant.

12:02.273 --> 12:03.373
I loved being pregnant.

12:03.408 --> 12:05.275
I know.

12:05.310 --> 12:07.010
And again,
I'm so sorry...

12:07.045 --> 12:08.412
You don't have
to keep saying
you're sorry.

12:08.446 --> 12:11.248
I just...
I feel helpless
to help you,

12:11.282 --> 12:13.150
and I can see that
you're still hurting.

12:13.185 --> 12:15.018
I don't want any help!

12:15.053 --> 12:16.086
Don't help!

12:17.321 --> 12:19.189
I don't want people
feeling sorry for me.

12:19.223 --> 12:22.025
I can't stand being pitied.

12:22.059 --> 12:25.094
And I don't want
to talk about
the baby, Grace.

12:25.128 --> 12:28.096
It's really hard for me
and it honestly doesn't
seem to

12:28.131 --> 12:29.365
do me any good
to talk about it.

12:29.399 --> 12:31.434
Okay. Let's talk
about something else,
anything else.

12:33.003 --> 12:34.404
It's really great
to see you.

12:34.438 --> 12:36.339
I missed you.

12:36.373 --> 12:38.374
I missed being able
to talk to you
anytime I wanted,

12:38.409 --> 12:41.011
anytime I needed.

12:41.045 --> 12:44.180
I mean, that's what's
so great about having
a best friend, right?

12:44.215 --> 12:45.448
You can tell your
best friend anything.

12:45.483 --> 12:48.184
Would you stop?

12:48.219 --> 12:50.053
I don't need to talk
about what happened.

12:50.088 --> 12:53.323
I totally understand
what you're saying about that.

12:53.358 --> 12:55.426
But maybe
I need to talk to you.

12:57.429 --> 12:59.130
Really.

12:59.164 --> 13:01.932
I can tell you things
I would never tell
anyone else.

13:01.967 --> 13:03.400
What can you tell me
that you can't tell
anyone else?

13:05.203 --> 13:07.037
About my trip to Zimbabwe.

13:07.072 --> 13:08.105
What about it?

13:08.139 --> 13:10.174
Well...

13:10.208 --> 13:12.075
It was an
amazing experience.

13:12.110 --> 13:14.044
You know, Jeff really
let me do a lot.

13:14.078 --> 13:15.412
He let me
watch him operate

13:15.446 --> 13:17.948
and I got to hold the...

13:17.982 --> 13:19.016
The babies?

13:21.353 --> 13:27.258
It's not like people
can stop saying
the word "baby" or "babies."

13:27.292 --> 13:29.994
I'm just going to have
to get used to it.

13:30.028 --> 13:35.099
So, get back
to what you were saying
about the babies.

13:35.134 --> 13:37.235
That's just what the
volunteers mostly do.

13:38.170 --> 13:40.304
Hold the little patients.

13:40.339 --> 13:42.039
You can tell anyone that.

13:42.074 --> 13:43.274
Yeah, I know.

13:43.308 --> 13:45.976
Get to the part that
you can only tell me.

13:46.011 --> 13:47.344
Is there a part
that you can only tell me

13:47.379 --> 13:49.313
or were you just
trying to make me feel
special or something

13:49.347 --> 13:50.381
to make me feel better?

13:51.450 --> 13:53.417
You can't make me feel
better, all right?

13:53.452 --> 13:55.319
So don't do that.

13:55.354 --> 13:58.356
Just be honest,
say what you're thinking.

13:58.391 --> 14:00.258
Geez, I wish more people
could be like Betty.

14:01.194 --> 14:02.995
I...

14:03.029 --> 14:04.330
I am like Betty.

14:05.232 --> 14:06.966
The old Betty.

14:25.185 --> 14:28.253
If all the guys
look like that over there,
I might volunteer.

14:28.287 --> 14:31.056
He's not from over there,
he's from over here.

14:31.091 --> 14:32.291
He's from California.

14:32.325 --> 14:34.059
He was over there
with his dad.

14:34.094 --> 14:35.194
His dad was one
of the doctors.

14:38.998 --> 14:41.100
Wait... You and this guy...

14:41.134 --> 14:42.168
Yep.

14:42.202 --> 14:43.336
(EXCLAIMING)

14:43.370 --> 14:45.304
I didn't mean
for it to happen,

14:47.140 --> 14:48.308
but I'm really
happy that it did.

14:48.342 --> 14:50.076
(LAUGHING)

14:59.464 --> 15:00.498
Why not Bunny?

15:00.532 --> 15:01.665
Because she's Bunny.

15:01.700 --> 15:04.301
Yeah. She is Bunny.

15:04.335 --> 15:06.669
She knows
everything there is to
know about the business

15:06.704 --> 15:08.705
and she knows Leo.
Who better than Bunny?

15:08.739 --> 15:10.640
Probably anyone.
Even you.

15:10.675 --> 15:11.708
Oh?

15:11.742 --> 15:13.543
I didn't mean that
like it sounded.

15:13.578 --> 15:15.679
How did you mean it?
I meant it in a good way.

15:15.713 --> 15:18.515
I meant, he could
have asked you.
I guess.

15:18.549 --> 15:21.585
Yeah, I guess,
but who wants it?

15:21.619 --> 15:24.321
I'm happy right here,
right now, you know.

15:24.355 --> 15:27.324
I'm sober, I have
a safe place to live,

15:27.359 --> 15:29.360
I have an honest job.

15:29.394 --> 15:31.362
I have my son
back in my life

15:31.396 --> 15:34.366
and my grandson and...

15:34.400 --> 15:36.668
What do I call Amy
now that you two
are living together?

15:36.703 --> 15:38.604
Amy.
Oh. Okay.

15:38.638 --> 15:40.539
Don't forget about Ollie.
You've got Ollie.

15:40.574 --> 15:41.574
What do I call Ollie?

15:44.379 --> 15:45.545
(SIGHS)

15:46.614 --> 15:47.814
We broke up,

15:47.848 --> 15:49.516
like a few weeks ago.

15:50.618 --> 15:53.587
What happened?
I'll tell you what happened.

15:53.621 --> 15:55.522
I couldn't make
a commitment either,

15:55.556 --> 15:57.423
not real commitment.

15:57.458 --> 16:01.661
She wanted a wedding
and a marriage

16:01.695 --> 16:04.631
and she wanted
to invite friends
and family and I

16:05.666 --> 16:07.500
didn't.

16:07.535 --> 16:08.668
Wait, "either"?
What do you mean
by "either"?

16:08.703 --> 16:11.371
Oh, so you're going
to marry Amy someday?

16:11.405 --> 16:12.772
I don't think
we want to get married.

16:12.807 --> 16:14.507
We like things
just like they are.

16:14.542 --> 16:18.712
You've been living together
for like what, a week now?

16:18.746 --> 16:21.348
You think Amy is going
to be happy with
just living together?

16:21.382 --> 16:23.550
Don't kid yourself.

16:23.584 --> 16:26.586
And don't tell Margaret
I said anything
about this, okay?

16:27.422 --> 16:29.589
(DOOR CLOSING)

16:29.623 --> 16:31.624
Hey, Mr. Petersen!
How are you?

16:38.432 --> 16:39.599
What's going on?

16:39.633 --> 16:41.768
Nothing.
Bunny's filling in
at your dad's office.

16:41.802 --> 16:43.503
Oh, geez.

16:43.537 --> 16:45.571
No wonder he's out
running loose today.
He didn't mention that.

16:45.606 --> 16:47.740
What happened
to his assistant?

16:47.775 --> 16:49.375
Who knows?

16:49.410 --> 16:50.743
You know.
Wouldn't you know?

16:50.778 --> 16:52.611
How would I know?
I know you know something

16:52.646 --> 16:54.547
'cause you're answering
questions with questions.

16:54.581 --> 16:58.351
Maybe she got tired
of working for him
after 25 years.

16:58.386 --> 17:00.654
I mean, think about it.
About 25 years.

17:00.688 --> 17:02.489
That's 300 months.

17:02.523 --> 17:05.325
That's thousands of weeks.

17:05.359 --> 17:06.626
1,300.

17:06.661 --> 17:07.761
How many days?

17:07.795 --> 17:11.598
365 times 25,
plus six for leap year...

17:11.632 --> 17:13.733
How many?
9,131.

17:13.767 --> 17:17.636
Can you imagine
spending 9,131 days
with anyone?

17:17.671 --> 17:20.472
I can't. Can you?

17:20.507 --> 17:21.773
I can't even stand
to think about it.

17:21.808 --> 17:25.377
It's like staring
into a giant black hole
in the universe

17:25.412 --> 17:27.313
and watching
your entire life
get sucked through it

17:27.347 --> 17:28.780
before you can
even grab on to it
for the ride.

17:28.815 --> 17:31.650
Maybe you're thinking
a little too much, you know?

17:31.685 --> 17:33.486
Just don't think about it.

17:37.758 --> 17:39.592
I can't quit
thinking about it.

17:39.626 --> 17:41.427
You'll see.
Once you start
thinking about it,

17:41.461 --> 17:44.363
about the hours
and the days and the
months and the years

17:44.398 --> 17:45.765
you're going
to spend with Amy,
things will change.

17:45.799 --> 17:48.367
And not for the better.
I don't care how
happy you are.

17:49.803 --> 17:51.704
I want out.
I don't care if you know,

17:51.738 --> 17:53.572
I don't care
if everyone knows,
I want out.

17:53.606 --> 17:55.341
Do you care
if Adrian knows?

17:55.375 --> 17:57.443
Stop saying that
out loud or someone
is going to tell her.

17:57.478 --> 17:59.578
Maybe it's better that way.
Because I can't.

17:59.613 --> 18:00.679
I can't tell her
I want to go.

18:00.714 --> 18:03.650
And I can't stay.
It's killing me.

18:03.684 --> 18:06.285
You tell her.
You know her best,
or you think you do.

18:06.319 --> 18:07.353
You tell her.

18:07.387 --> 18:08.420
I don't even talk to her.

18:08.455 --> 18:10.489
If and when
I do talk to her,

18:10.523 --> 18:12.424
it's not going to be
to tell her that you
want out of your marriage.

18:12.458 --> 18:13.758
Geez, she just
lost a baby.

18:13.793 --> 18:17.461
So did I.

18:26.503 --> 18:30.439
Wow. That's a little change
from the apron, huh?

18:30.474 --> 18:31.574
You look nice, Bunny.

18:31.608 --> 18:33.509
You look very, um,
professional.

18:35.712 --> 18:37.313
What's your problem?

18:37.347 --> 18:39.614
Mr. Petersen is just
waiting on his steaks.

18:39.649 --> 18:40.782
Here you go.

18:40.817 --> 18:43.518
Tell Teresa I already put
the marinade on,

18:43.553 --> 18:45.587
she doesn't have
to do a thing,
just throw them on the grill.

18:45.621 --> 18:47.456
Thanks, sweetheart.
Bunny.

18:49.626 --> 18:52.528
I prefer dead cows
to people any day.

18:53.664 --> 18:55.565
So, is Leo okay?

18:55.599 --> 18:59.435
No, he is not okay.
He is short-tempered
and cranky.

19:00.571 --> 19:02.338
But,

19:02.373 --> 19:06.576
for the exception
of Camille, I guess,
everybody understands.

19:06.610 --> 19:07.744
Understands what?

19:07.778 --> 19:09.712
That you all had
a rough year.

19:09.747 --> 19:13.717
And right now
your dad is a sensitive guy
with a short temper

19:13.751 --> 19:15.686
but a big heart.

19:15.720 --> 19:18.622
Yeah, a big heart
and yet not big enough.

19:18.656 --> 19:19.689
We have that in common.

19:30.634 --> 19:32.368
(SIGHING)

19:38.775 --> 19:40.809
Leo, what are
you doing here?

19:42.812 --> 19:46.414
I'm here to ask you
if you could please
come back to work.

19:46.448 --> 19:48.316
I took another job.
I start Monday.

19:48.350 --> 19:49.650
Come on, Camille.
Don't go to a new job.

19:49.684 --> 19:51.585
It's not too late for you
to change your mind.

19:51.620 --> 19:54.389
I'm afraid it is, Leo.
It is too late.

19:55.491 --> 19:57.658
Thanks for coming by,

19:57.693 --> 20:00.595
but let's not make this
any harder on me than
it already has been.

20:00.630 --> 20:03.732
Well, if it's so difficult,
why did you leave?

20:03.767 --> 20:06.402
Why not?
Why not?

20:06.436 --> 20:09.705
Because you're important
to the company.

20:10.674 --> 20:12.508
The company needs you.

20:13.811 --> 20:15.545
Okay, I need you.

20:15.580 --> 20:17.414
Please. Come back.

20:17.782 --> 20:19.550
No.

20:19.584 --> 20:20.751
Sorry, Leo,
I've made up my mind.

20:20.786 --> 20:22.587
I don't want to be there.

20:22.621 --> 20:23.655
I don't want
to work for you.

20:23.689 --> 20:24.723
To be blunt.

20:24.757 --> 20:26.791
To be honest.
Is that honest?

20:26.825 --> 20:28.392
That's as honest
as I can get.

20:28.427 --> 20:30.561
Why don't you want
to work for me
all of a sudden?

20:31.396 --> 20:32.463
I just don't.

20:32.497 --> 20:33.564
There has to be a reason.

20:33.598 --> 20:35.498
No, there doesn't.
There's no reason?

20:36.433 --> 20:37.667
(SIGHS)

20:37.701 --> 20:40.469
I think you know
the reason, Leo.
I think I don't.

20:40.503 --> 20:41.670
You want to take a guess?

20:41.705 --> 20:42.771
No.

20:42.805 --> 20:44.639
But you know
I'd like to come back,

20:44.673 --> 20:46.441
so if you go
to the new job

20:46.475 --> 20:48.443
and you don't like it
and you change your mind...

20:48.477 --> 20:50.478
I won't, and going back
to what you just said,

20:50.512 --> 20:51.746
I don't know
how you feel.

20:54.817 --> 20:56.417
All right.

20:56.451 --> 20:58.553
Well, I feel that

20:59.688 --> 21:02.457
people make
mistakes sometimes,

21:02.491 --> 21:05.660
and then, unfortunately,
they have to live with
those mistakes

21:06.695 --> 21:08.362
and make the best of it.

21:08.397 --> 21:10.398
Yes. Even you.

21:10.432 --> 21:12.400
I just said that.
You said "people."

21:12.834 --> 21:15.336
You know I meant me.

21:15.370 --> 21:16.604
I guess what
I'm saying is

21:16.638 --> 21:19.340
I can't live
with your mistakes.

21:19.374 --> 21:21.475
And I don't want to be
a part of your "making
the best of it,"

21:21.510 --> 21:23.344
whatever that means.

21:23.378 --> 21:25.379
So, thank you
for dropping by,

21:26.715 --> 21:27.781
but don't drop by again.

21:31.520 --> 21:33.554
All right.

21:33.588 --> 21:36.424
I won't drop by again
and I'll stop asking you
to come back to work.

21:39.495 --> 21:41.563
So I guess this is it.

21:42.465 --> 21:43.599
This is it.

21:43.633 --> 21:45.701
You always did have
to have the last word.

22:16.119 --> 22:17.953
See for yourself.

22:18.889 --> 22:20.056
(LAUGHING)

22:21.759 --> 22:24.061
Hi, John. Hi.

22:24.095 --> 22:26.764
Hi. I hope you don't
mind if we drop by.

22:26.798 --> 22:28.932
I stopped by the bakery
to pick up some things
for dinner

22:28.966 --> 22:31.968
and I thought
I'd drop off a cake
for you guys.

22:32.003 --> 22:33.903
That is so sweet.

22:33.938 --> 22:35.071
Yeah. Would you
like to sit down?

22:35.106 --> 22:38.709
Oh, no, we can't stay.
I'm cooking spaghetti tonight.

22:38.743 --> 22:39.877
I didn't know you cook.

22:39.911 --> 22:42.012
Well, Ricky does
most of the cooking.

22:42.047 --> 22:44.982
I don't know how
to cook very many things
other than spaghetti, huh?

22:49.755 --> 22:53.957
So, this is a little
more awkward than
I thought it might be.

22:53.992 --> 22:58.696
Look, I just feel really
badly that you don't like
that I'm living with Ricky.

22:58.730 --> 23:00.831
Or that John and I
are living with Ricky.

23:00.866 --> 23:03.668
And I know he says
he doesn't care,
but he does care.

23:03.702 --> 23:04.736
We both do.

23:04.770 --> 23:06.837
Oh, no, honey.

23:06.872 --> 23:10.007
I don't think it's the worst
thing that the two of you
are living together.

23:10.041 --> 23:15.846
No, we don't approve
but we don't not approve.

23:15.880 --> 23:17.781
It may work out,
it may not.

23:17.815 --> 23:20.884
I just didn't like
hearing about it
from somebody else.

23:20.918 --> 23:22.819
But we're over that now.

23:22.853 --> 23:23.920
Are you?

23:23.954 --> 23:26.022
Amy, we've all just
got to stay focused

23:26.056 --> 23:30.059
on what is best
for this little man
right there.

23:30.094 --> 23:32.662
And if you and Ricky
can work things out

23:32.696 --> 23:34.630
so that you can raise
your son together,

23:34.665 --> 23:35.965
I'm all for it.

23:35.999 --> 23:39.768
And I'm all for Ricky
having a, uh...

23:39.803 --> 23:41.904
Stable, loving relationship.

23:41.938 --> 23:44.006
Even if you're not married.

23:44.040 --> 23:46.942
Amy, are you okay
with not being married?

23:46.976 --> 23:49.911
With living with Ricky
without any kind
of commitment?

23:49.946 --> 23:53.081
Shakur, that's a little
personal, don't you think?

23:54.049 --> 23:55.950
Sorry.

23:55.984 --> 23:59.920
But as long as
the question is
out there, are you?

23:59.954 --> 24:01.655
I really am.

24:02.657 --> 24:03.823
I am.

24:03.858 --> 24:06.760
I think that being married
can make Ricky feel trapped.

24:06.794 --> 24:09.596
And I think being married
is a good thing
for a lot of people,

24:09.631 --> 24:11.599
but I don't think
it would be a good
thing for Ricky and me.

24:11.633 --> 24:12.734
You know what?

24:12.768 --> 24:15.703
You are a smart cookie.

24:15.738 --> 24:17.906
I like you, Amy,
I really do.

24:17.941 --> 24:20.676
And I'm glad that
you stopped by here.

24:20.710 --> 24:22.845
You're always welcome here.

24:22.880 --> 24:26.749
And it's nice to see
you and John in my kitchen,
feels like family.

24:26.783 --> 24:28.083
Thanks.

24:28.118 --> 24:29.785
No French fries.

24:31.988 --> 24:33.655
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

24:35.925 --> 24:37.859
Hey, Ash, how's the road?
Good.

24:37.894 --> 24:39.962
That's great.
Where are you now,
the middle of Texas?

24:39.996 --> 24:41.696
You must be around
the middle of Texas.

24:41.731 --> 24:43.631
Are you to
San Antonio yet?

24:43.666 --> 24:44.766
You've got to stop
and visit the Alamo.
It's amazing.

24:44.800 --> 24:47.668
We're kind of past
San Antonio.

24:47.703 --> 24:50.772
Yeah, well, turn
around and go back.
Believe me, it's worth it.

24:50.806 --> 24:54.009
Well, we're not
just past San Antonio.
We're way past it.

24:54.043 --> 24:55.777
You can't be
way past it yet.

24:55.812 --> 24:57.646
Last time
you called me,
you were in El Paso.

24:57.680 --> 24:59.582
Yeah, but we just had
a couple of cappuccinos
and kept driving.

24:59.616 --> 25:01.017
Where are you?
We're here.

25:01.051 --> 25:02.618
<i>You're where?</i>

25:02.653 --> 25:03.686
In Florida.

25:03.721 --> 25:04.754
You can't be
in Florida already.

25:04.788 --> 25:05.989
Oh, I can,
because I am.

25:06.023 --> 25:07.624
What?

25:07.658 --> 25:08.858
We're at the
house already.

25:08.892 --> 25:10.926
Toby's grandmother's house.
It's nice.

25:10.961 --> 25:12.662
But you just left,
like, yesterday.

25:12.696 --> 25:13.929
We left a week ago.

25:13.964 --> 25:15.965
So you're there with
Toby's grandmother?

25:15.999 --> 25:19.835
Uh, we're at
Toby's grandmother's
house, yeah.

25:19.869 --> 25:20.902
With his grandmother?

25:20.937 --> 25:22.837
Uh...

25:22.872 --> 25:25.039
No.
But she's coming.

25:25.074 --> 25:26.907
We got here
a couple of weeks early

25:26.942 --> 25:28.843
and she's
still in New York,
but she's coming.

25:28.877 --> 25:31.679
All right, Ashley.
Well, I'm happy
you made it.

25:31.713 --> 25:33.981
And there's a lot
you can learn in Florida.
A lot of history there.

25:35.750 --> 25:37.684
I miss you.
Yeah, I miss you,
too, Dad.

25:38.119 --> 25:40.688
And, um...

25:40.722 --> 25:43.057
Thanks for
letting me do this.

25:43.091 --> 25:44.959
It really is
kind of fun.

25:47.062 --> 25:48.796
I love you.
Good night.

25:48.830 --> 25:50.097
Good night, Ashley.

25:54.736 --> 25:55.836
Pass the ketchup.

25:56.939 --> 25:58.039
(KNOCKING)

26:07.049 --> 26:08.650
Hey, I was hoping
you'd be here.

26:08.685 --> 26:09.785
Yeah, I'm here.

26:09.819 --> 26:11.587
I haven't
seen you in a while,

26:11.621 --> 26:12.888
so I thought
I'd drop by
and say hello.

26:12.922 --> 26:14.022
Your mothers tell you
to come and talk to me?

26:14.056 --> 26:15.657
No.

26:15.691 --> 26:16.758
You're the one
who told them?

26:16.792 --> 26:17.825
They didn't tell you
I told them?

26:17.860 --> 26:19.694
No.
Tell them what?

26:19.728 --> 26:21.629
You told them
Amy and I are
living together.

26:21.663 --> 26:22.763
The whole thing
is ridiculous.

26:22.797 --> 26:23.864
You're not old enough to
have your own apartment,

26:23.898 --> 26:25.031
much less
your own family.

26:25.066 --> 26:26.600
Yeah, maybe,

26:26.634 --> 26:27.868
but we do have
our own apartment

26:27.902 --> 26:30.671
and our own family,
and that's how it is.

26:30.705 --> 26:31.872
That place is too small
to raise your son

26:31.906 --> 26:33.740
in that tiny apartment
with him right next to you.

26:33.775 --> 26:36.710
People live
in tinier apartments
with more than one kid.

26:36.744 --> 26:38.612
I hope you're
not here to tell me
you're having another kid.

26:38.646 --> 26:41.014
No, no, I'm not.
I'm just here because

26:41.049 --> 26:43.650
you're Amy's dad
and I want to be on
good terms with you

26:43.684 --> 26:44.952
and the rest
of the family.

26:44.986 --> 26:46.786
And I'd like you
to come over and
visit us sometime,

26:46.821 --> 26:48.622
and I know
Amy would like that.

26:48.656 --> 26:49.990
I'm not going to do that,
so you don't have to
worry about that.

26:50.024 --> 26:53.060
I'm not
worried about that.
Why wouldn't you?

26:53.094 --> 26:55.094
'Cause I don't want
to see where you're
sleeping with my daughter.

26:55.129 --> 26:56.863
You've seen
my apartment before.

26:56.897 --> 26:58.831
Not with the
two of you in it.
The three of us.

26:58.866 --> 27:00.700
And the three of us
are really happy there.

27:00.734 --> 27:02.835
Yeah? Well,
sooner or later the
honeymoon is going to be over

27:02.870 --> 27:04.904
and then we'll see
how happy the
three of you are.

27:04.939 --> 27:07.040
I guess there's
a honeymoon period
with all relationships,

27:07.074 --> 27:08.909
whether you're married
or just living together.

27:08.943 --> 27:10.577
That's what the
marriage is for.

27:10.612 --> 27:11.945
That's why you make
a legally binding commitment.

27:11.979 --> 27:13.881
To keep you together
after the honeymoon is over.

27:13.915 --> 27:16.016
To keep you together
long after you want
to be there.

27:16.050 --> 27:18.719
If there comes a time
when Amy doesn't
want to be there,

27:18.754 --> 27:19.754
she can just walk away.

27:19.789 --> 27:21.056
And so can you.
That's why this whole

27:21.090 --> 27:22.757
living-together thing
doesn't work.

27:22.792 --> 27:24.893
It works for us.
For right now.

27:24.927 --> 27:27.762
You crazy teenagers
think that that's
what life is all about.

27:27.797 --> 27:29.764
The right now.

27:29.798 --> 27:31.966
I think that's what
Buddhists think life is
all about. The right now.

27:32.000 --> 27:33.802
So now
you're a communist?
What?

27:33.836 --> 27:36.771
No. I'm not
a communist or a Buddhist

27:36.805 --> 27:37.939
or anything but
in love with Amy.

27:37.973 --> 27:39.607
Why can't I just
be in love with Amy?

27:39.641 --> 27:40.675
Because that's not enough.

27:40.709 --> 27:42.610
It is for Amy.
It's not for me.

27:42.644 --> 27:44.879
All right, well,
Amy wanted you
to come over

27:44.913 --> 27:47.682
and have dinner with us.
She's making spaghetti.

27:47.716 --> 27:48.850
She makes the worst
spaghetti in the world.

27:48.885 --> 27:50.686
(CHUCKLES) I know.

27:50.720 --> 27:51.987
It doesn't even
have real meat in it.
I know.

27:52.022 --> 27:53.723
You want to eat
meatless spaghetti
the rest of your life?

27:53.757 --> 27:56.626
We could bring
Moose with us.

27:56.660 --> 27:58.962
She just wants to feel
like what we're doing
is okay with you.

27:58.997 --> 28:01.665
She doesn't have to
have your approval,
but she wants it.

28:01.699 --> 28:03.734
Actually, she does
need my approval.

28:03.769 --> 28:05.570
You're 18, she's not.

28:05.604 --> 28:06.971
If I want to stop
the two of you
from living together,

28:07.005 --> 28:08.005
legally, I could.

28:08.040 --> 28:09.807
But you're not
going to, are you?

28:10.609 --> 28:11.742
No, I'm not.

28:11.776 --> 28:12.810
She loves you.

28:12.844 --> 28:15.613
She loves you more.
Yeah.

28:15.647 --> 28:16.981
But isn't that the way
life's supposed to be?

28:17.015 --> 28:18.783
No.
Come on.

28:18.817 --> 28:20.751
Tell you what,
I'll have dinner over there

28:20.786 --> 28:22.687
when you put
a ring on her finger,

28:22.721 --> 28:24.889
and I don't even want
to see that happen until
she's graduated from college.

28:24.923 --> 28:26.891
That's a really,
really long time.

28:26.925 --> 28:28.793
Yeah. So is the
rest of your life.

28:37.701 --> 28:39.035
I honestly think
it's good for Ashley

28:39.069 --> 28:40.737
to go off
on this adventure,

28:40.772 --> 28:42.072
to get away from
her house for a while.

28:42.106 --> 28:43.841
Yeah, well, look
where that got me.

28:43.875 --> 28:45.877
Telling Grace to go off
on her adventure.

28:45.912 --> 28:47.679
She doesn't even
want to see me
her first night home.

28:47.714 --> 28:49.681
Yeah, I know.

28:49.715 --> 28:51.750
I'd feel that way
if Peter went off

28:51.784 --> 28:53.952
and didn't call me
when he got back,

28:53.986 --> 28:55.920
but of course,
Ashley's not my girlfriend,

28:55.955 --> 28:58.023
she's just a friend,
a good friend.

28:58.057 --> 28:59.124
Your best friend.

28:59.159 --> 29:00.993
She was my best friend.

29:01.027 --> 29:03.996
But hey, I've got
a new best friend.

29:04.031 --> 29:05.832
Who's that?
Peter.

29:05.866 --> 29:07.800
He's not your best friend,
he's your boyfriend.

29:07.834 --> 29:09.902
Yeah, that too.

29:09.936 --> 29:11.070
Oh, here he is.

29:16.110 --> 29:17.811
Sorry I'm late.

29:20.982 --> 29:23.151
Griffin didn't tell you
I was coming, did he?

29:23.185 --> 29:24.719
I don't care.

29:24.753 --> 29:26.087
I assumed he was
bringing Grace

29:26.122 --> 29:28.156
since you said
she was back.

29:28.190 --> 29:30.926
So where is Grace?
She wanted to
see her family.

29:30.960 --> 29:32.761
I mean, that's
understandable, right?

29:32.795 --> 29:34.195
She did just
get back in last night.

29:34.230 --> 29:35.230
Right.
Right.

29:37.967 --> 29:39.167
I don't know,

29:39.201 --> 29:40.968
but if Griffin went away
for a couple of weeks

29:41.003 --> 29:42.970
and on his
first night back
he didn't see me,

29:43.004 --> 29:45.906
I think I'd be accusing
someone of cheating.

29:45.940 --> 29:49.876
Ooh. Whoa!
We're talking
about Grace here.

29:49.910 --> 29:52.746
And I would never
cheat on you.

29:52.780 --> 29:53.847
Grace would never
cheat on me.

29:53.881 --> 29:55.182
And I would never
cheat on her.

29:55.216 --> 29:56.917
You think
she cheated on me?

29:56.952 --> 29:58.953
She's on a medical mission.
Who would she cheat with?

30:01.023 --> 30:02.123
Yummy.

30:02.158 --> 30:04.025
Is Jack eating with us
or is it just the two of us?

30:04.060 --> 30:07.062
Oh, let's see,
it's the four,
five, seven of us.

30:07.096 --> 30:09.865
Tom and Rachel
and the kids and Jack?

30:09.899 --> 30:11.066
Yes. And Jack.

30:11.101 --> 30:13.101
So, can you set
the dining room
table, please?

30:13.136 --> 30:16.237
Okay, I think
I'm just gonna
eat in my room, in bed.

30:16.271 --> 30:18.005
I'm so jet-lagged.

30:18.040 --> 30:19.874
I don't think
I could stay awake
through a meal.

30:19.908 --> 30:21.842
Oh. Well, you should have
slept in this morning.

30:22.277 --> 30:23.977
I needed to see Adrian.

30:24.011 --> 30:26.012
You could have
seen her tomorrow.

30:26.046 --> 30:27.980
I'm surprised
you didn't need
to see Grant.

30:28.015 --> 30:29.114
He's not coming
over tonight?

30:29.149 --> 30:31.016
No, I'm too tired
to see Grant.

30:31.051 --> 30:32.918
Really, can't I just
take a plate of food
upstairs and eat?

30:32.953 --> 30:34.186
Honey, no.
You need to get back

30:34.221 --> 30:35.922
on your normal schedule
as soon as possible.

30:35.956 --> 30:38.191
I mean, you have to be
back at school
on Monday. Okay?

30:38.225 --> 30:40.727
So, why don't you just
eat with all of us,

30:40.762 --> 30:42.763
stay awake
as long as you can,

30:42.797 --> 30:44.732
and then go to bed,
and then wake up
at your usual time tomorrow?

30:44.767 --> 30:46.834
I'll try, but I don't know,
I don't know if
I'm going to make it.

30:46.869 --> 30:47.869
(CELL PHONE BEEPS)

30:50.874 --> 30:51.974
It's Grant.

30:52.008 --> 30:53.208
Oh, well, tell him
he's welcome

30:53.242 --> 30:55.744
to come over and
eat with the rest of us.

30:55.778 --> 30:57.011
Although, I prefer
the two of you not spend
the night together.

30:57.046 --> 30:58.246
You know,
just take it one night...

30:59.849 --> 31:02.116
Grace, what's going on?

31:02.150 --> 31:04.251
Nothing.
I just told Grant
I'd see him tomorrow.

31:05.987 --> 31:07.220
I just don't feel comfortable
with having him here

31:07.255 --> 31:09.155
when Jack's
in the next room.

31:09.190 --> 31:10.990
Which is probably
the real reason

31:11.025 --> 31:12.859
you let that woman
and her two children
move into the guest house

31:12.893 --> 31:14.794
and you put Jack
right next door to me.

31:14.828 --> 31:15.929
(CELL PHONE BEEPS)

31:15.963 --> 31:18.131
So, who are you texting?

31:18.165 --> 31:20.966
It's not Grant.
I can tell it's not Grant.

31:21.001 --> 31:22.168
No, you can't.

31:22.202 --> 31:24.136
Is it that guy
you met on your trip?

31:24.170 --> 31:27.840
What? What guy
did I meet on my trip?

31:27.874 --> 31:30.209
Mom, please.
I did not meet
a guy on my trip.

31:32.246 --> 31:34.881
Jeff sends pictures,
you know.

31:34.915 --> 31:36.716
Jeff can send
all the pictures he wants,

31:36.750 --> 31:38.084
it doesn't mean
I met somebody.

31:38.119 --> 31:43.090
I mean, I met people,
but not any special
guy kind of people.

31:44.092 --> 31:45.793
Who's that?

31:46.128 --> 31:49.030
Oh. That guy? I

31:49.065 --> 31:50.765
resuscitated him.

31:50.799 --> 31:51.933
(LAUGHS)

31:51.967 --> 31:53.101
Standing up?

31:53.135 --> 31:55.970
Yeah, that's how they
like to do it over there.

31:56.004 --> 31:59.739
You know, it's better
for the lungs to be upright.

31:59.774 --> 32:01.808
Honey,
Jeff already told me.

32:01.842 --> 32:02.909
That I slept with that guy?

32:03.210 --> 32:04.811
You did what?

32:04.845 --> 32:06.846
Okay, don't get upset.
Please don't get upset.

32:06.880 --> 32:08.815
I'm already upset enough.
I don't know what
I was thinking.

32:08.849 --> 32:11.918
Grace, this is why
you don't have sex
in high school.

32:11.952 --> 32:16.022
Well, this is why you do.

32:16.057 --> 32:19.827
Grace! You can't just sleep
with every guy you meet.

32:19.862 --> 32:21.763
This is going to be
the last one.

32:21.797 --> 32:23.765
Honey, you said that
Jack was going to be
the only one

32:23.799 --> 32:25.067
for the rest of your life.

32:25.101 --> 32:27.069
And I know
you believed it,
even though I didn't.

32:27.103 --> 32:29.906
And then Grant,
you said you were
in love with Grant.

32:29.940 --> 32:33.175
I am! Or I was. I love him.

32:33.210 --> 32:34.977
I never said Grant was
going be the last one.

32:36.146 --> 32:38.181
I think I'm in love
with Daniel, Mom.

32:38.215 --> 32:41.017
And not in the same way
I was in love with Jack.
Or Grant.

32:41.051 --> 32:42.785
And the way
you're in love with Daniel

32:42.819 --> 32:44.753
is not the way
you're gonna be
in love with the next guy,

32:44.787 --> 32:45.987
or the next guy after that.

32:46.022 --> 32:47.022
Probably not.

32:47.056 --> 32:48.056
Probably not?

32:48.091 --> 32:50.091
Ugh, Grace, I was just
trying to make a point.

32:50.126 --> 32:51.159
Well, can you hurry up
and make it?

32:51.194 --> 32:53.194
Because he's
on his way over here.

32:54.864 --> 32:55.897
JACK: Who's on his way
over here?

32:56.765 --> 32:57.865
Oh, God.

32:57.899 --> 32:59.099
I'm sorry,
but I live here.

32:59.133 --> 33:01.935
I couldn't help
but hear you
coming down the stairs.

33:01.970 --> 33:03.804
New boyfriend, huh?

33:03.838 --> 33:05.205
If you say a word
to Madison or to your
new friend Grant,

33:05.239 --> 33:07.741
or to anybody, anybody,
I will...

33:07.776 --> 33:08.943
Grace, stop.

33:08.977 --> 33:11.078
I'm not going to say
anything to anyone.

33:11.112 --> 33:13.947
But I can't wait to meet him.
So, you cheated, huh?

33:13.981 --> 33:15.048
Hmm.

33:15.082 --> 33:16.917
See, it's easier
than you thought, isn't it?

33:16.951 --> 33:19.219
I used to be like that.
But then I met someone
I really love.

33:19.253 --> 33:21.821
(SCOFFS) You'd cheat
with me if I let you.

33:21.856 --> 33:23.055
Actually I wouldn't.

33:23.090 --> 33:24.123
Oh, yeah?
Yeah.

33:29.896 --> 33:30.897
Hmm.

33:32.833 --> 33:35.135
Okay, I am just
gonna go eat
in the guest house

33:35.169 --> 33:37.804
with Tom and Rachel
and the kids,
and so will you.

33:37.838 --> 33:39.139
Don't you want
to meet this guy,
see if you like him?

33:39.173 --> 33:41.742
Oh, I like him.
I mean, I like you,

33:41.776 --> 33:43.177
I like Grant,
I liked Ricky and Ben.

33:43.211 --> 33:45.913
I've liked all the guys
Grace has been out with.

33:45.948 --> 33:47.015
But I think
she's gonna be going out

33:47.049 --> 33:48.917
with a lot more guys
after this.

33:48.951 --> 33:52.053
So, I just wish
she would stop having sex
until she's a little older

33:52.087 --> 33:54.089
and ready to make
a commitment. And you too.

33:54.123 --> 33:55.924
I'm not having sex.

33:55.958 --> 33:57.958
Well, as Grace pointed out,
how long is that gonna last?

34:04.799 --> 34:06.766
I hope not much longer.

34:07.034 --> 34:08.201
(DOORBELL RINGS)

34:19.880 --> 34:21.982
Hi. Uh, is Grace home?

34:23.819 --> 34:24.886
Are you Jack?

34:24.920 --> 34:25.920
Are you Daniel?

34:31.882 --> 34:33.916
nner.

34:33.951 --> 34:36.786
He was asked
to be at the family dinner,
he's living with the family.

34:36.820 --> 34:38.922
That doesn't mean
he's cheating on you
with Grace.

34:38.956 --> 34:40.690
Well, it's her
first night home

34:40.724 --> 34:42.692
and it's the first time
he's ever broken a date
with me.

34:42.726 --> 34:46.062
It's step one
to cheating. It's step one
to him breaking up with me.

34:46.097 --> 34:48.699
Well, I say
let go and let God.

34:48.733 --> 34:50.033
If you really want
to know if he loves you,

34:50.068 --> 34:52.068
set him free and see
if he comes back to you.

34:52.103 --> 34:55.039
Oh, like Jesse or...
What was that other guy?

34:55.072 --> 34:56.907
Yeah. Like that.

34:56.942 --> 34:58.075
Yeah, you'd like that,
wouldn't you?

34:58.110 --> 34:59.877
If I didn't have
a boyfriend, too.

34:59.911 --> 35:02.780
I'd love that.
I'm sick of Jack.

35:02.814 --> 35:05.015
I want to go out
and have some fun.

35:05.049 --> 35:06.983
Some girlfriend fun.

35:07.018 --> 35:11.988
I want to go to the mall
and hang out at some hangout.

35:12.022 --> 35:16.093
I want to meet some new guys
and have some new experiences.

35:16.127 --> 35:18.963
Well, I don't!
Oh, don't call him.

35:22.134 --> 35:23.835
(PHONE RINGING)

35:25.838 --> 35:27.806
Hello.
Reverend Stone?

35:27.840 --> 35:29.741
Reverend Stone?
Madison?

35:29.776 --> 35:31.843
Honey, it's Madison.
Hi, Madison.

35:31.878 --> 35:35.914
I just want to tell you
something that I feel that
Jack is never gonna tell you.

35:35.948 --> 35:38.016
Should you do that?
No, you shouldn't.

35:38.050 --> 35:39.685
Is that Lauren?

35:39.719 --> 35:41.820
Lauren's with Madison.
Hi, Lauren.

35:41.854 --> 35:44.056
Jack is having a bit
of an emotional breakdown.

35:44.090 --> 35:45.857
I just talked to him.

35:45.892 --> 35:47.859
He sounded okay to me,
happy even.

35:47.894 --> 35:50.729
He would never
tell you this,

35:50.763 --> 35:53.065
but Jack really doesn't want
to go to Arizona to school.

35:53.099 --> 35:57.036
He really
wants you guys to move back
and to take your old job back.

35:57.070 --> 35:59.939
You know,
he just wants to
live with you guys

35:59.973 --> 36:02.075
and make up
for this last year.

36:02.109 --> 36:05.878
He hates living with
the Bowmans and he just...

36:05.913 --> 36:08.048
He wants to live here
and just go to school here.

36:10.084 --> 36:11.852
Javelina.

36:11.886 --> 36:13.153
Well, thank you for
letting me know,
Madison.

36:13.187 --> 36:16.023
I really appreciate it.
I'll be back in touch.
Good night.

36:17.092 --> 36:18.892
Yeah, right there.

36:18.927 --> 36:20.060
Oh!

36:20.094 --> 36:21.929
Madison wants us to
move back.

36:23.931 --> 36:26.799
Okay, you are
in so much trouble.

36:33.741 --> 36:35.943
You might as well go home.
I don't think she's going
to wake up.

36:35.977 --> 36:37.044
She'll wake up.

36:37.078 --> 36:39.079
All right,
suit yourself.

36:40.949 --> 36:42.050
Hey, where is everyone?

36:42.084 --> 36:45.787
How come no one
is in the kitchen?

36:46.790 --> 36:47.857
Who are you?

36:47.891 --> 36:50.927
Grant, this is Daniel.
Daniel, this is Grant.

36:50.962 --> 36:53.062
Nice to meet you.
What happened to Grace?

36:53.097 --> 36:56.065
You know, that's
a very good question.

36:56.100 --> 36:58.801
Maybe she fell apart
when our church fell apart.

36:58.835 --> 37:01.837
You know, one minister
after another, one guy...

37:03.039 --> 37:05.007
Ah, never mind.

37:05.041 --> 37:07.744
I don't know
if you know this or not, but
Grace used to be a Christian.

37:07.778 --> 37:09.078
So what?
I'm a Christian.

37:09.113 --> 37:10.913
Me, too.
I've never even been to church

37:10.948 --> 37:13.049
and I'm betting I'm
the only Christian here.

37:21.091 --> 37:22.925
I have to talk to Grant.

37:27.064 --> 37:28.865
I'll call you tomorrow?

37:31.936 --> 37:34.070
I'll probably see you later,
'cause I'll be right upstairs.

37:38.975 --> 37:40.909
Hi. Good night.

37:42.911 --> 37:44.078
Grant,

37:45.814 --> 37:48.882
I'm really sorry,
but I...

37:51.853 --> 37:54.054
I met somebody else.
Obviously.

37:54.088 --> 37:56.690
I'm really sorry.

37:56.725 --> 37:57.724
Me, too.

37:59.827 --> 38:02.028
But hey, things happen, and

38:04.065 --> 38:05.866
I hope we can be
friends, Grace.

38:05.900 --> 38:08.836
You do?

38:08.870 --> 38:13.841
Okay, that's not
what I was expecting,
but that's so nice.

38:16.044 --> 38:18.746
Wait a minute. That's
a little bit too nice.

38:19.915 --> 38:22.016
What'd you do?
Good night, Grace.

38:43.070 --> 38:44.070
Adrian?

38:49.710 --> 38:50.944
I've been waiting for you.

38:52.080 --> 38:54.013
I need to talk to you.
I need to talk to you.

38:56.984 --> 38:58.852
I know what
you're going to say, Ben.

38:58.886 --> 39:01.021
No.

39:01.055 --> 39:03.857
No, I don't think you do know
what I'm going to say.

39:03.891 --> 39:06.726
Okay, maybe I don't,

39:09.063 --> 39:12.032
but here's what I want
to say to you.

39:16.037 --> 39:20.040
I don't blame you if you
want to run away from home.

39:22.077 --> 39:25.779
I don't blame you if
you can't take this anymore,

39:25.814 --> 39:28.749
if you don't
want to be with me.

39:28.783 --> 39:32.820
I've been
horrible these past
two months, really horrible.

39:34.022 --> 39:36.724
I've just been so hurt, Ben.

39:37.993 --> 39:42.964
Losing Mercy
hurt me more than
I knew I could be hurt.

39:42.998 --> 39:46.902
And a tough girl like me
doesn't know how to be hurt.

39:48.737 --> 39:51.005
I stopped allowing myself
to be hurt years ago.

39:53.775 --> 39:55.710
But this,

39:55.744 --> 39:58.012
what happened to us,

39:58.047 --> 40:01.816
that went
right through that wall
that I always put up,

40:01.851 --> 40:04.820
and it crushed me.

40:04.854 --> 40:07.823
And I've been trying
to pick up the pieces,

40:07.858 --> 40:10.059
but there are just
so many pieces,

40:10.093 --> 40:15.063
it was overwhelming
and terrifying and
just exhausting.

40:17.099 --> 40:19.968
But I don't want
to lose you, Ben.

40:20.936 --> 40:22.871
I really don't.

40:22.905 --> 40:24.939
I love you
more than you know.

40:26.041 --> 40:29.811
And I'm just asking
for some time,

40:31.113 --> 40:34.048
just a little more
of your time.

